                <alternative value="ti">
                    <title>TI Instructions</title>
                    <p><em>One Sample z-test for the proportion (p)</em>
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Choose <code style="inline">STAT/TESTS/5:1-PropZTest</code>. </li>
                        <li>Note: Use arrows to navigate through the menu. </li>
                        <li>1-PropZTest </li>
                        <li>p<sub>o</sub>: Enter the null value from the null hypothesis. </li>
                        <li>x: Enter number of airplanes with coliform bacteria in the drinking
                            water. </li>
                        <li>n: Enter the sample size. </li>
                        <li>prop &#8800; p<sub>o</sub> &lt; p<sub>o</sub> &gt; p<sub>o</sub>: Choose
                            the relevant form of the alternative hypothesis. </li>
                        <li>You should see: <image style="inline"
                                src="../../webcontent/image505.jpg"
                                alt="TI calculator output: 1-PropZTest
            p_0: .035
            x: 40
            n: 316
            prop&ne;p_0  &lt;p_0  &gt;p_0
            Calculate    Draw"
                            />
                        </li>
                        <li>Arrow down and choose CALCULATE, then press ENTER. </li>
                    </ul>
